The paper discusses a decentralized self-regulatory framework that utilizes software agents embedded in physical assets of supply-demand systems. This involves the use of Internet of Things technologies and standardized concepts, which suggests a focus on multi-agent systems and artificial intelligence (cs.MA, cs.AI). The framework also involves the assessment of optimality and system constraints, which suggests a focus on control systems and cyber-physical systems (cs.SY, cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for online adjustments incentivized by utilities, system operators, and policy makers, which suggests a focus on distributed computing and data centers (cs.DC).
